{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "rbac-userroles-e2e",
    "name": "RBAC \u2013 User Roles (/admin/rbac/users/{user_id}/role)",
    "description": "E2E tests for the user role assignment API.\n\nRoutes covered:\n  GET    /api/v1/admin/rbac/users/{user_id}/role\n  PUT    /api/v1/admin/rbac/users/{user_id}/role\n  DELETE /api/v1/admin/rbac/users/{user_id}/role\n\nFolder execution order:\n  1. setup            \u2014 register + Gmail OTP + verify-email + login\n                        (captures ur_access_token \u2014 plain user, no RBAC permissions yet)\n                        also registers a second target user (ur_target_user_id) to be assigned roles\n  2. auth-guard       \u2014 401 on all three routes with no Authorization header\n  3. rbac-guard       \u2014 403 on all three routes with valid JWT but no permissions\n  4. owner-bootstrap  \u2014 POST /owner/assign promotes the acting user to owner\n                        (grants rbac:read + rbac:manage; RBAC middleware reads DB per request)\n  5. happy-path       \u2014 GET (no role yet \u2192 404) \u2192 PUT (assign role) \u2192 GET (assert role) \u2192 DELETE (remove role) \u2192 GET (assert gone \u2192 404)\n  6. conflict-guard   \u2014 409 when attempting to modify own role or reassign owner\n  7. not-found        \u2014 404 when user_id resolves but has no role (GET/DELETE)\n                        and 422 when role_id is unknown (PUT)\n  8. validation       \u2014 422/400/413 input-error cases for PUT\n\nGuard order (handler):\n  GET    /rbac/users/{user_id}/role   : JWTAuth \u2192 RBAC.Require(rbac:read)   \u2192 handler\n  PUT    /rbac/users/{user_id}/role   : JWTAuth \u2192 RBAC.Require(rbac:manage) \u2192 handler\n  DELETE /rbac/users/{user_id}/role   : JWTAuth \u2192 RBAC.Require(rbac:manage) \u2192 handler\n\nThe admin router applies AllowContentType(\"application/json\") before JWTAuth, so PUT\nrequests in auth-guard must carry Content-Type: application/json.\n\nEnvironment variables required:\n  bootstrap_secret   \u2014 must match BOOTSTRAP_SECRET in the running server's .env\n  gmail_test_email   \u2014 Gmail address for OTP receipt\n  gmail_access_token \u2014 OAuth2 token for Gmail API reads\n\nNotes on what is NOT covered here (covered by unit/service tests):\n  - DB / store errors \u2192 500              \u2014 handler_test.go, service_test.go\n  - UUID parse errors in service          \u2014 service_test.go\n  - ErrLastOwnerRemoval DB trigger        \u2014 service_test.go\n\nRun `make _e2e-db-clean` and `make _e2e-kv-clean` before each suite run.\nRequires TRUSTED_PROXIES=127.0.0.1/32 in .env.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "const n = (pm.collectionVariables.get('_req_seq') | 0) + 1;",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_req_seq', n);",
          "const ip = '10.' + ((n>>16)&0xff) + '.' + ((n>>8)&0xff) + '.' + (n&0xff);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', ip);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "setup",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /register \u2192 201 (setup acting user)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const email = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email');",
                  "if (!email) { console.error('[ERROR] gmail_test_email not set in environment \u2014 add it to environment.json.'); }",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('ur_acting_email', email);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('ur_acting_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('message field present and non-empty', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
                  "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set \u2014 skipping Gmail fetch'); return; }",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for verification email to arrive in Gmail...');",
                  "const start = Date.now(); while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Done waiting. Querying Gmail API (async)...');",
                  "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Verify your\" newer_than:1h');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({ url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q=' + query + '&maxResults=3', method: 'GET', header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token } }, (err, res) => {",
                  "    if (err) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail list failed:', err); return; }",
                  "    if (res.code === 401) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail token expired'); return; }",
                  "    const msgs = res.json().messages;",
                  "    if (!msgs || !msgs.length) { console.warn('[WARN] No matching email found.'); return; }",
                  "    pm.sendRequest({ url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/' + msgs[0].id + '?format=full', method: 'GET', header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token } }, (err2, res2) => {",
                  "        if (err2) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed:', err2); return; }",
                  "        const msg = res2.json(); let body = '';",
                  "        const parts = msg.payload && msg.payload.parts;",
                  "        if (parts && parts.length) { const p = parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/plain') || parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/html'); if (p && p.body && p.body.data) body = atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')); }",
                  "        else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.body && msg.payload.body.data) { body = atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')); }",
                  "        if (!body) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode email body.'); return; }",
                  "        const match = body.match(/(?<!#)\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
                  "        if (!match) { console.warn('[WARN] No 6-digit OTP found.'); return; }",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('ur_acting_code', match[1]);",
                  "        console.log('[INFO] OTP stored in collection variable \"ur_acting_code\":', match[1]);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"display_name\": \"URActingUser\", \"email\": \"{{ur_acting_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{ur_acting_password}}\"}", "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}},
            "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","register"]}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /verify-email \u2192 200 (verify acting user)",
          "event": [
            {"listen": "prerequest", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["const code = pm.collectionVariables.get('ur_acting_code'); if (!code) { console.error('[ERROR] ur_acting_code is empty.'); }"]}},
            {"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));", "pm.test('message includes \"verified\"', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('verified'));"]}}
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{ur_acting_email}}\", \"code\": \"{{ur_acting_code}}\"}", "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}},
            "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/verify-email", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","verify-email"]}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /login \u2192 200 (capture ur_access_token + ur_acting_user_id)",
          "event": [
            {"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(body.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('ur_access_token', body.access_token);",
              "const payload = JSON.parse(atob(body.access_token.split('.')[1].replace(/-/g,'+').replace(/_/g,'/')));",
              "pm.test('user.id present', () => pm.expect(payload.sub).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('ur_acting_user_id', payload.sub);",
              "console.log('[INFO] Captured ur_access_token and ur_acting_user_id:', payload.sub);"
            ]}}
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{ur_acting_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{ur_acting_password}}\"}", "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}},
            "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","login"]}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /register \u2192 201 (setup target user)",
          "event": [
            {"listen": "prerequest", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "const base = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email') || 'test@example.com';",
              "const parts = base.split('@');",
              "const targetEmail = parts[0] + '+urtarget@' + parts[1];",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('ur_target_email', targetEmail);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('ur_target_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');"
            ]}},
            {"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
              "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
              "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set \u2014 skipping Gmail fetch for target user'); return; }",
              "const targetEmail = pm.collectionVariables.get('ur_target_email');",
              "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for target user verification email...');",
              "const start = Date.now(); while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
              "console.log('[INFO] Done waiting. Querying Gmail API for target user...');",
              "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Verify your\" to:' + targetEmail + ' newer_than:1h');",
              "pm.sendRequest({ url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q=' + query + '&maxResults=3', method: 'GET', header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token } }, (err, res) => {",
              "    if (err) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail list failed:', err); return; }",
              "    if (res.code === 401) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail token expired'); return; }",
              "    const msgs = res.json().messages;",
              "    if (!msgs || !msgs.length) { console.warn('[WARN] No matching email found for target user.'); return; }",
              "    pm.sendRequest({ url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/' + msgs[0].id + '?format=full', method: 'GET', header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token } }, (err2, res2) => {",
              "        if (err2) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed:', err2); return; }",
              "        const msg = res2.json(); let body = '';",
              "        const parts = msg.payload && msg.payload.parts;",
              "        if (parts && parts.length) { const p = parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/plain') || parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/html'); if (p && p.body && p.body.data) body = atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')); }",
              "        else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.body && msg.payload.body.data) { body = atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')); }",
              "        if (!body) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode target email body.'); return; }",
              "        const match = body.match(/(?<!#)\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
              "        if (!match) { console.warn('[WARN] No 6-digit OTP found.'); return; }",
              "        pm.collectionVariables.set('ur_target_code', match[1]);",
              "        console.log('[INFO] OTP stored in collection variable \"ur_target_code\":', match[1]);",
              "    });",
              "});"
            ]}}
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"display_name\": \"URTargetUser\", \"email\": \"{{ur_target_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{ur_target_password}}\"}", "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}},
            "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","register"]}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /verify-email \u2192 200 (verify target user)",
          "event": [
            {"listen": "prerequest", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["const code = pm.collectionVariables.get('ur_target_code'); if (!code) { console.error('[ERROR] ur_target_code is empty.'); }"]}},
            {"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));", "pm.test('message includes \"verified\"', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('verified'));"]}}
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{ur_target_email}}\", \"code\": \"{{ur_target_code}}\"}", "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}},
            "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/verify-email", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","verify-email"]}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /login (target user) \u2192 200 (capture ur_target_user_id)",
          "event": [
            {"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(body.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
              "const payload = JSON.parse(atob(body.access_token.split('.')[1].replace(/-/g,'+').replace(/_/g,'/')));",
              "const id = payload.sub;",
              "if (id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('ur_target_user_id', id); console.log('[INFO] Captured ur_target_user_id:', id); } else { console.warn('[WARN] Could not extract target user ID from JWT sub.'); }",
              "pm.test('target user ID captured', () => pm.expect(pm.collectionVariables.get('ur_target_user_id')).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);"
            ]}}
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{ur_target_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{ur_target_password}}\"}", "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}},
            "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","login"]}
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "auth-guard",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /rbac/users/{user_id}/role \u2014 no Authorization \u2192 401",
          "event": [{"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));", "pm.test('code is missing_token', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('missing_token'));"]}}],
          "request": {"method": "GET", "header": [{"key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}"}], "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/admin/rbac/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/role", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","admin","rbac","users","00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001","role"]}}
        },
        {
          "name": "PUT /rbac/users/{user_id}/role \u2014 no Authorization \u2192 401",
          "event": [{"listen": "test", "script": {"type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));", "pm.test('code is missing_token', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('missing_token'));"]}}],
          "request": {"method": "PUT", "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}"}], "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"role_id\": \"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\", \"granted_reason\": \"test\"}", "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}}, "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/admin/rbac/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/role", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","admin","rbac","users","00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001","role"]}}
        },
